article.headline: Long Beach St. 74, Montana 56
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. -- Eugene Phelps scored 19 points and Larry Anderson added 17 as Long Beach State defeated Montana 74-56 on Saturday night. Casper Ware scored 12 points and T.J. Robinson had 10 points and 10 rebounds for the 49ers (17-10). Brian Qvale scored 17 points and Art Steward 13 for the Grizzlies (19-8). Long Beach State maintained a consistent cushion for the entire BracketBuster game, which matched the leaders of the Big West and Big Sky conferences. Montana got as close as 54-46 in the second half. But the 49ers pulled away with a 14-2 run over the next 4:41, sparked by Phelps' three consecutive baskets.
